The Schenectady Gazette of 3-18-25 ran a shot of Maurice and Barbara B. in a dancing pose, obviously taken on this occasion, as they are in the same clothes and it looks like they are aboard a ship. The caption includes the information that they  &quot;are on their way to Switzerland to begin a continental tour.&quot;
<a href="http://fultonhistory.com/Newspaper 8/Schenectady NY Gazette/Schenectady NY Gazette 1925 Grayscale/Schenectady NY Gazette 1925 Grayscale - 1353.pdf#xml=http://fultonhistory.com/dtSearch/dtisapi6.dll?cmd=getpdfhits&amp;u=50eaa30d&amp;DocId=2644533&amp;Index=Z:\Index O-G-T&amp;HitCount=1&amp;hits=59+&amp;SearchForm=C:\inetpub\wwwroot\Fulton_New_form.html&amp;.pdf" rel="nofollow">fultonhistory.com/Newspaper%208/Schenectady%20NY%20Gazett...</a>
The New York Sun's 3/14/25 account makes it clear the Bennetts were seeing off their teenaged daughter as she sailed with Maurice on the Cunard Lines'  SS Aquitania.  Their pending divorce is mentioned.
<a href="http://fultonhistory.com/Newspaper 18/New York NY Sun/New York NY Sun 1925/New York NY Sun 1925 - 2034.pdf#xml=http://fultonhistory.com/dtSearch/dtisapi6.dll?cmd=getpdfhits&amp;u=668e0d2c&amp;DocId=2740360&amp;Index=Z:\Index I-E-V&amp;HitCount=1&amp;hits=439+&amp;SearchForm=C:\inetpub\wwwroot\Fulton_New_form.html&amp;.pdf" rel="nofollow">fultonhistory.com/Newspaper%2018/New%20York%20NY%20Sun/Ne...</a>
The dance partnership was not to last much longer, however.   A news report from December, 1925:   &quot;N e w York—Barbara Bennett has quit Maurice Mouvet and he now has Eleanora Ambrose for a dancing partner. Barbara says she left because $500 a week was not enough.  Maurice says the reason was temperament. &quot;
